item.title: welp
item.author: me@robxu9.com (Robert Xu)
item.description: That was quick. What have I been up to? Things I’ve done lately include: studying for CSE 320, which is System Architecture. I feel like I’m slow on the uptake with this class, whatnot with muxes and ALUs… working on CSE 306, which is implementing a simple grep without libc. So just Linux system calls. Not bad, just time consuming. Also I gave up trying to make descriptive errors and just dumped errno.
